 une maison très propre, agréable dans un quartier très pratique et chaleureux; Héléna est sympathique disponible et de bon conseil; sa maîtrise du français est parfaite; elle nous a fait le plaisir de nous offrir des pâtisseries typiques; le jardin est agréable, on peut manger dehors; les magasins sont a proximité a pied ainsi que le bord de mer; pour le centre ville les fainéants prendront les transports en commun (Héléna a prévu les cartes d'abonnement et divers guides)  ou la voiture, les courageux iront à pieds le long du Douro; on arrive sans problème a se faire comprendre en français ou en anglais dans le quartier;
seul petit bémol le chien de la voisine qui esseulé a partagé son malheur en pleurant un peu;
bref un séjour que je recommande chaudement.

We stayed here for a month. I will give you "+" and "-":
+Zack was responding very fast and able to help, came for checkin when we came;
+perfect location, Chelsey is clean and safe;
+clean bed and towels (towels were new when we came);
+everything you need for cooking at the kithen;
+condition helped us because it was VERY hot in July;
+good wifi and tv.
- the appartment was VERY small, it was really difficult to stay for 2 person, we didn't have space to eat together;
-everything is very old, didn't look good;
-it was very dirty, the floor, the bathroom, kitchen, I tried to clean the room, but it was really not enough, I didn't want to touch 90% of this place;
-cockroaches!!!! If don't like them, it's not your place;
-old plumbing, water was always plumbing, it was annoying;
-rather expensive, host increased the price after I asked for booking...
